Package edu.washington.cs.cse490h.lib

Class Summary
Callback Generic class to facilitate use of callbacks Also provides a static helper function to get an object of Method that can be passed to the constructor of this class Example: To get a Method object for the method public foo(String str) in class Test: String[] paramTypes = {"java.lang.String"}; Method method = Callback.getMethod("foo", this, paramTypes); Callback cb = new Callback(method, this, "fooTest"); The above code snippet assumes that it is written inside class Test, hence the use of this.
CommandsParser CommandsParser -- parses file and keyboard commands COMMANDS ARE CASE SENSITIVE.
EmulatedNode Keeps track of information about an emulated node The emulated is the Router's abstraction of the client.
EmulationCommandsParser Parser for the Emulator.
Emulator Manager that runs under a single emulated node on the client machine.
Event Class that represents the various types of events within the managers
Manager Abstract class defining generic routines for running network code under the MessageLayer
MessageLayer Class with main method that starts up a Manager.
Node Node -- Class defining the interface and basic functionality of a node.
NodeContainer A container that represents an address.
NodeServer In a separate thread, this class listens to incoming messages from the router and stores the data received.
Packet Packet defines the MessageLayer packet headers and some constants.
PersistentStorageReader File reader abstraction.
PersistentStorageWriter Class that nodes use to write to persistent storage.
Replay Class that handles deterministic replay in both the simulator and emulator.
Router Simply routes packets in the network and stores queued packets to failed nodes.
SimulationCommandsParser Parser for the Simulator commands.
Simulator Manages a simulation, where all nodes are running in the same process, in the same thread
SynopticLogger Class to handle logging of Synoptic events.
Utility Provides some useful static methods.
